ct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":71,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":80,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":115,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Ewenlode was born in 1144, in Coughton, Warwickshire, England as the son of Ewenlode and Mrs Ewenlode. He married Mrs. Robert de Ewenlode in 1169, in Coughton, Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1144–":"1144–Surnud","1144–Male":"1144–Surnud","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","1148":"1148","1169":"1169","1224":"1224","1144":"1144","Abt 1165":"umbes 1165","before 1144":"enne 1144","1165":"1165","of Coughton, Warwick, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Coughton, Alcester, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Coughton, 